@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements..."
@NEXT "Installation"
@PREV "Contents"
@TOC "MAIN"

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~

  In order to use this collection you will need:

  * An AMIGA ;-) with at least Kick 2.0+ (3.0 recommended)

  * A properly installed MagicWB of Martin Huttenloher
    or (under WB 2.0/2.1) NickPrefs

  * If you want to use a boot picture, you need a program like
    PicBoot V2.7

  * Internet access - so you can send me e-mail to @{"REGISTER" LINK "Author"}!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Installation" "Installation..."
@NEXT "Author"
@PREV "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

  Quite simple: just drop the pictures into your 'pattern-directory'
  and click on the 'PaletteAGA/PaletteECS' icon to get the right
  colors. Finaly choose a background with the 'WBPattern' program!
  
  To install a boot picture you will need a program like PicBoot V2.7
  (available on AmiNET/util/boot).

  Have fun!

@ENDNODE


